reserve m for Nat;
theorem
Th11: ((i is_quadratic_residue_mod m & i,j are_congruent_mod m) implies j is_quadratic_residue_mod m)
proof
assume that
A1: i is_quadratic_residue_mod m
and
A2: i,j are_congruent_mod m;
consider x being Integer such that A3: ( ( ( x ^2 ) - i ) mod m ) = ( 0 ) by A1,CKB11:def 1;
m divides ( i - j ) by A2,INT_2:15;
then A4: ( ( i - j ) mod m ) = ( 0 ) by CKB3:1;
( ( ( x ^2 ) - j ) mod m ) = ( ( ( ( x ^2 ) - i ) + ( i - j ) ) mod m )
.= ( ( ( ( ( x ^2 ) - i ) mod m ) + ( ( i - j ) mod m ) ) mod m ) by NAT_D:66
.= ( 0 ) by A3,A4,NAT_D:65;
hence thesis by CKB11:def 1;
end;
